{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id62db5651-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t25/s5127"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5127"},"text":"§ 5127.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Procedure","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In any election heretofore or hereafter held under the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1934-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 1934","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/984"},"text":"48 Stat. 984","children":[],"tail":") ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t25/s5101"},"text":"25 U.S.C. 5101","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], on the question of excluding a reservation from the application of the said Act or on the question of adopting a constitution and bylaws or amendments thereto or on the question of ratifying a charter, the vote of a majority of those actually voting shall be necessary and sufficient to effectuate such exclusion, adoption, or ratification, as the case may be: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided, however","children":[],"tail":", That in each instance the total vote cast shall not be less than 30 per centum of those entitled to vote."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id62db5652-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-06-15/ch260/s1"},"text":"June 15, 1935, ch. 260, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/378"},"text":"49 Stat. 378","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id62db5653-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id62db5654-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"tex